## Description
The **Package Files **task allows to package the outputs of workflow tasks on a given branch, for example to prepare them for delivery according to the rules of the destination system.

> Note

The contents of the output package are organized in a folder structure. It is possible to include any of the output files of all previous tasks on the same execution branch.

It is possible to include up to 20,000 files within a single package. The maximum package size supported is 40GB.

> Important

The input of the **Package Files **task should not be a task with multiple output branches or a task with a single output branch that can produce multiple chunks in order to avoid conflicts or the incorrect chunk to be processed.

## Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Output **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an element to the structure of the **Package**:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)The possible options are:

**Folder**: the output folder produced produced by the previous task in the workflow, or a newly defined folder

- **Archive**: a ZIP archive that may contain folders and files

- **Content**: the output file(s) produced by the previous task in the workflow

- Add as many elements to the package structure as required; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Select an element to configure its settings. The required fields vary depending on the selected element:

[Folder](/doxee-platform/docs/package-files-batch-workflow-task-reference#folder)

- [Archive](/doxee-platform/docs/package-files-batch-workflow-task-reference#archive)

- [Content](/doxee-platform/docs/package-files-batch-workflow-task-reference#content)

### Folder
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name identifying the folder element.

- *(optional) *Enable the **Dynamic **option to copy the folder name from the output of the previous task, and fill in the required fields:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Select the **Source **task from which to copy the folder name.

- In the **Pattern **field, enter the filename pattern to use to identify the folder name from the previous task.

> Important

Make sure that the pattern matches a single folder; otherwise, an error will occur.

- In the **Fragment **field select the preferred option to inherit the folder name:

**Full name**: full name, including base name and file extension

- **Base name**: only the base name, without extension

- In the **Template **field, enter the static folder name to use (for example: *folder_1*).

### Archive
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name identifying the archive element.

- In the **Content **section, select the archive **Format:**

**Zip**

- **7z**

- **Gzip**

- **Tar**

- *(optional) *Enable the **Dynamic **option to copy the archive name from the output of the previous task, and fill in the required fields:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Select the **Source **task from which to copy the archive name.

- In the **Pattern **field, enter the filename pattern to use to identify the archive name from the previous task.

> Important

Make sure that the pattern matches a single archive; otherwise, an error will occur.

- In the **Fragment **field select the preferred option to inherit the archive name:

**Full name**: full name, including base name and file extension

- **Base name**: only the base name, without extension

- In the **Template **field, enter the static archive name to use (for example: *archive.zip*).

- Enable the **Encrypt **option to protect the archive contents with a custom password.![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

This option is only available for the archive formats Zip and 7z.

Select the **Key **resource to be used as password (see [Archive Key Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/archive-key-resource-reference)).

### Content
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name identifying the content element.

- Select the **Source **task from which to import the files or folders.

> Important

The input of the **Package Files **task should not be a task with multiple output branches or a task with a single output branch that can produce multiple chunks in order to avoid conflicts or the incorrect chunk to be processed.

- In the **Include **field, enter the filename pattern to use to identify the files and folders to include in the package.

- *(optional) *In the **Exclude **field, enter the filename pattern to use to identify the files and folders to exclude from the package.

> Tip

It is possible to include or exclude:

all files belonging to a folder (for example: *output/*.xml*)

- only files or folders whose name matches a regular expression (for example: *BB**)

> Important

When receiving files from a [Transform Files (DT)](/doxee-platform/docs/transform-files-dt-batch-workflow-task-reference) task via an "All Files" branch, files are organized in folders, one for each configured DT Writer.

To include (or exclude) the correct files, use the following syntax:

- specify the name of the DT Writer (folder) and then the filename pattern (for example: *WriterName/*.xml*) 

- select all folders (*) and then the filename pattern (for example: **/*.xml*)
